  "tcmHistory": {
    "en": "First appeared in Divine Husbandman's Classic of the Materia Medica, classified as middle class with no categorisation between Baishao and Chishao. Baishao first appeared in Collection of Commentaries on the Materia Medica.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "始載於《神農本草經》，列為中品。但無赤芍、白芍之分，統稱為芍藥。白芍藥則見於《本草經集注》。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "始载于《神農本草经》，列为中品。但無赤芍、白芍之分，统稱为芍药。白芍药則見于《本草经集注》。\n"
  },
  "tcmTraditionalUsage": {
    "en": "Baishao, derived from the roots of the white peony, is a bitter tasting herb that is sour and cool in nature,affecting the liver and spleen meridians. It subdues hyperactivity of the liver, relieves pain, checks excessive perspiration, nourishes the blood and regulates menstruation. Its use is indicated where a patient is suffering from symptoms including headaches and dizziness; costal and abdominal pain; diarrhea; spasmodic pain of the limbs; anaemia; menstrual disorders; spontaneous sweating and night sweating.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "白芍是補血藥，味苦、酸、甘，藥性微寒，歸肝、脾經，能養血調經、平肝止痛、斂陰止汗。常用於頭痛、眩暈、脅肋疼痛、四肢攣痛、血虛、月經不調、自汗及盜汗等。\n",
    "zh-Hans": "白芍是补血药，味苦、酸、甘，药性微寒，歸肝、脾经，能养血调经、平肝止痛、斂阴止汗。常用于头痛、眩暈、脅肋疼痛、四肢攣痛、血虚、月经不调、自汗及盜汗等。\n"
  },
  "tcmModernResearch": {
    "en": "Baishao is a central nervous system suppressant, an antipyretic, an antibiotic and can relax and dilate blood vessels to decrease blood pressure, and calm the smooth muscles of the intestines. It has been used extensively in clinical studies to treat intestinal cramps, muscle spasms and constipation with good results.\n",
    "zh-Hant": "【白芍】Modern Research內容待翻譯補充。",
    "zh-Hans": "【白芍】Modern Research內容待翻譯补充。"
  },
